# Documentation & Learning

- Every non-trivial feature updates `docs/` or README section: purpose, env vars, run commands.
- ADRs for architecture choices (payments provider, auth) in `docs/adr/NNN-title.md`.
- Explain **why**, not just what; link to Jira/Notion ticket when available.

```markdown
## Order webhooks
- Env: `CONEKTA_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
- Run locally: `stripe listen` or Conekta sandbox dashboard
- Failure mode: orders stay `pending_payment` until webhook retries
```

- Code comments only for non-obvious business rules (e.g., bat drop calculation for youth leagues).
- New env vars -> `.env.example` + learner-documenter note in PR description.
- Follow [human-writing-style.mdc](./human-writing-style.mdc): no em dashes, section symbols, emoji markers, or decorative Unicode in docs.
